│ simplifies to %for.start for both incoming edges after SROA/instcombine-like  │
│ reasoning. The vectorizer’s recurrence handling assumes a non-degenerate      │
│ recurrence and places the \"broadcast\" (of the start value) in the wrong     │
│ block when it turns the recurrence into a VPFirstOrderRecurrencePhi. The      │
│ broadcast ends up in the header (%vector.body) and is used as the PHI’s       │
│ backedge incoming value from that same block, breaking dominance.\n\n2.       │
│ Analyzing opt's Log:\n- SCEV classifies %for and %for.next as invariant       │
│ (%for.start). This implies there is no true recurrence.\n- The error shows:   │
