│ ... [ %vector.recur.init, %vector.ph ], [ %broadcast.splat2, %vector.body     │
│ ]\". The incoming from %vector.ph (the preheader) is fine. The incoming from  │
│ %vector.body (the header) is not: the value must be defined in the            │
│ predecessor latch block, not the header. Thus, the broadcast was sunk/placed  │
│ in the wrong block, or the PHI was wired to the wrong predecessor.\n- The     │
│ assertion in processLoop verifies the whole function after vectorization. The │
│ location indicates the error is introduced during VPlan execution             │
│ (LVP.executePlan), specifically during recipe placement/sinking.\n\n3. Root   │
│ Cause Analysis:\nThe VPlan builder/transformer does not detect that the       │
│ \"recurrence\" is a degenerate case with identical incoming values after      │
│ simplification. It still constructs a VPFirstOrderRecurrencePhi and a         │
│ broadcast of the start value, but sinks/emits the broadcast in the vector     │
│ loop header (%vector.body) and connects it as the backedge incoming to the    │
│ PHI from %vector.body, instead of from the latch block. Under normal          │
│ circumstances, the backedge incoming should come from the latch predecessor,  │
│ and any broadcast needed on the backedge must be placed in that latch block   │
│ or earlier, so that it dominates the terminator of the predecessor.\n\nThis   │
│ misplacement likely comes from one of:\n- VPWidenPHIRecipe::executeImpl       │
│ creating the backedge incoming using a value built in the header builder      │
│ rather than latch builder.\n- A VPlan transform (like sinkScalarOperands() or │
│ canonicalization) choosing an invalid sink target for a dead                  │
│ instruction/broadcast in degenerate recurrences and placing it into the       │
│ header block (%vector.body) as a convenience.\n- Wiring of blocks in VPlan    │
│ where the incoming from the backedge is recorded as coming from the header    │
│ instead of the latch, when the recurrence simplifies.\n\nGiven the symptom    │
│ text and typical code structure, the fix is to ensure: (a) degenerate         │
│ recurrences are treated as invariants (no VPFirstOrderRecurrencePhi), or (b)  │
│ the broadcast used as backedge incoming is placed in and taken from the latch │
│ predecessor, not the header.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\n- VPlan.h: add    │
